    &lt;CommentText&gt;My mother in law is 96 and has been in bed for three weeks with awful leg/foot ulcers that should have been treated in hospital three months ago, she has to see a podiatrist every month or she has a lot of pain (she has no flesh on the soles of her feet due to operations that did not go to plan) we have asked that a podiatrist sees her before the physios try to get her to stand, firstly to reduce her pain and secondly she would have more confidence in trying to stand, the doctor says that the inhouse podiatrist will only see people if they are diabetic! mother in law is not. There is no other podiatrist available that is allowed into the hospital. It seems absolutely crazy to me and the doctor that the inhouse podiatrist can not see her. Surely it would help in mobilizing her in a less painful way, and quicker . What do you suggest we do please as her regular podiatrist is not allowed into the hospital. Kind Regards.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
